significantly increasing.\n   - `emailservice`, `paymentservice`, and `shippingservice` showed noticeable variations in `rrt_max` during the fault, though not as pronounced as `adservice`.\n\n### Detected Metrics\n\n- The metrics with the most significant changes, based on the change ratio, are:\n  1. `rrt` for `adservice`\n  2. `rrt_max` for `adservice`\n  3. `node_cpu_usage_rate` for `aiops-k8s-05`\n\n### Hypotheses\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"rrt\", \"rrt_max\", \"node_cpu_usage_rate\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increased node CPU usage rate which could impact the performance of pods running on this node.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate increase from 14.1% to 20.81% with a change ratio of 0.3844.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increased response times impacting service performance.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt increased with a change ratio of 1.2957 for adservice-0.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nIn conclusion, the root cause seems primarily related to increased CPU usage on `aiops-k8s-05`, which might have contributed to the degraded performance of services, notably `adservice`."}
